  <!-- ===== 1. ABOUT THIS AGREEMENT ===== -->
  <h2>1. About This Agreement</h2>
  <div class="about-section">
    <h3>What Type of Tenancy Is This?</h3>
    <p>This is a <strong>Private Residential Tenancy (PRT)</strong> governed by the Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016. A PRT is the only type of tenancy that can be granted for a private residential let in Scotland.</p>

    <h3>Key Features of a PRT</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>No fixed end date:</strong> The tenancy continues until properly ended by either party</li>
      <li><strong>Security of tenure:</strong> The Tenant can only be evicted on specific statutory grounds</li>
      <li><strong>Tribunal process:</strong> The Landlord must obtain an eviction order from the First-tier Tribunal for Scotland</li>
      <li><strong>Rent protection:</strong> Rent increases are regulated and can be challenged</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>HMO Status</h3>
    <p>This property is a <strong>House in Multiple Occupation (HMO)</strong> licensed under the Civic Government (Scotland) Act 1982. Additional obligations apply to both Landlord and Tenant regarding shared facilities, fire safety, and occupancy limits.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-notice">
    <div class="legal-notice-title">Scottish Government Model Terms</div>
    {{#if uses_model_tenancy_terms}}
    <p>This agreement is based on the Scottish Government's model PRT terms, providing a standardised framework designed to reduce disputes and ensure compliance.</p>
    {{else}}
    <p>This agreement uses bespoke terms tailored to meet the specific requirements of this tenancy while remaining compliant with the Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016.</p>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <!-- ===== 2. THE PARTIES ===== -->
  <h2>2. The Parties</h2>
  <div class="parties-section">
    <div class="party-block">
      <div class="party-role">Landlord</div>
      <div class="party-details-text">
        <strong>{{landlord_full_name}}{{#if landlord_2_name}} and {{landlord_2_name}}{{/if}}</strong><br>
        <span class="address-text">{{landlord_address}}</span><br>
        <span class="email-text">{{landlord_email}}</span> | {{landlord_phone}}
      </div>
    </div>

    {{#if landlord_reg_number}}
    <div class="party-block">
      <div class="party-role">Landlord Registration</div>
      <div class="party-details-text">
        Registration Number: <strong>{{landlord_reg_number}}</strong><br>
        <em>(Antisocial Behaviour etc. (Scotland) Act 2004)</em>
        {{#if registration_authority}}<br>Registered with: {{registration_authority}}{{/if}}
        {{#if registration_expiry}}<br>Valid until: {{formatUKDate registration_expiry}}{{/if}}
      </div>
    </div>
    {{else}}
    <div class="legal-notice warning">
      <div class="legal-notice-title">Important</div>
      <p>The Landlord must be registered with the local council under the Antisocial Behaviour etc. (Scotland) Act 2004. Registration details will be provided.</p>
    </div>
    {{/if}}

    {{#if agent_name}}
    <div class="party-block">
      <div class="party-role">Landlord's Letting Agent</div>
      <div class="party-details-text">
        <strong>{{agent_name}}</strong><br>
        <span class="address-text">{{agent_address}}</span><br>
        <span class="email-text">{{agent_email}}</span> | {{agent_phone}}
        {{#if agent_reg_number}}<br>Registration: {{agent_reg_number}}{{/if}}
      </div>
    </div>
    {{/if}}

    <div class="party-block">
      <div class="party-role">Tenant{{#if multiple_tenants}}s{{/if}}</div>
      <div class="party-details-text">
        {{#each tenants}}
        <strong>{{add @index 1}}. {{this.full_name}}</strong>{{#if this.dob}} (DOB: {{formatUKDate this.dob}}){{/if}}<br>
        <span class="email-text">{{this.email}}</span>{{#if this.phone}} | {{this.phone}}{{/if}}{{#unless @last}}<br><br>{{/unless}}
        {{/each}}
      </div>
    </div>

    {{#if guarantor_name}}
    <div class="party-block">
      <div class="party-role">Guarantor</div>
      <div class="party-details-text">
        <strong>{{guarantor_name}}</strong><br>
        <span class="address-text">{{guarantor_address}}</span><br>
        <span class="email-text">{{guarantor_email}}</span> | {{guarantor_phone}}
      </div>
    </div>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <!-- ===== 3. THE PROPERTY ===== -->
  <h2>3. The Property</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">3.1</span> The Landlord lets to the Tenant the property described in Schedule 1 for use as a private residential dwelling.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">3.2</span> This property is licensed as a House in Multiple Occupation (HMO) under the Civic Government (Scotland) Act 1982.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">3.3</span> The Tenant has exclusive use of their designated bedroom and shared access to communal facilities as detailed in Schedule 1.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">3.4</span> The Landlord warrants that the property meets the Repairing Standard as required by the Housing (Scotland) Act 2006.</p>

  <table class="data-table">
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Property Address</td>
      <td class="value address-text">{{property_address}}</td>
    </tr>
    {{#if hmo_licence_number}}
    <tr>
      <td class="label">HMO Licence Number</td>
      <td class="value">{{hmo_licence_number}}</td>
    </tr>
    {{/if}}
    {{#if furnished_status}}
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Furnished Status</td>
      <td class="value">{{furnished_status}}</td>
    </tr>
    {{/if}}
    {{#if council_tax_band}}
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Council Tax Band</td>
      <td class="value">{{council_tax_band}}</td>
    </tr>
    {{/if}}
  </table>

  <!-- ===== 4. THE TENANCY ===== -->
  <h2>4. The Tenancy</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.1</span> This is a <strong>Private Residential Tenancy (PRT)</strong> under the Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.2</span> The tenancy start date is <strong>{{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}}</strong>.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.3</span> This tenancy has <strong>no fixed end date</strong>. It continues until ended by either party following the correct legal procedures.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.4</span> The tenancy cannot be converted to any other type of tenancy.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.5</span> The Tenant has security of tenure and can remain in the property as long as they comply with the tenancy terms and no valid eviction ground applies.</p>

  <table class="data-table">
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Tenancy Type</td>
      <td class="value">Private Residential Tenancy (PRT)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Start Date</td>
      <td class="value">{{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="label">End Date</td>
      <td class="value">No fixed end date</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Governing Law</td>
      <td class="value">Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016</td>
    </tr>
  </table>

  <!-- ===== 5. RENT & PAYMENTS ===== -->
  <h2>5. Rent and Payments</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.1</span> The Tenant shall pay the Rent of <strong>£{{rent_amount}}</strong> per {{rent_period}} in advance on the <strong>{{rent_due_day}}</strong> of each {{rent_period}}.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.2</span> Payment shall be made by {{payment_method}} to the account specified in Schedule 2.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.3</span> The first payment of <strong>£{{first_payment}}</strong> is due on <strong>{{formatUKDate first_payment_date}}</strong>.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.4</span> Rent must be paid without deduction or set-off unless legally entitled.</p>

  <table class="data-table">
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Rent Amount</td>
      <td class="value">£{{rent_amount}} per {{rent_period}}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Payment Due</td>
      <td class="value">{{rent_due_day}} of each {{rent_period}}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Payment Method</td>
      <td class="value">{{payment_method}}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="label">First Payment</td>
      <td class="value">£{{first_payment}} on {{formatUKDate first_payment_date}}</td>
    </tr>
    {{#if rent_includes}}
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Rent Includes</td>
      <td class="value">{{rent_includes}}</td>
    </tr>
    {{/if}}
    {{#if rent_excludes}}
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Rent Excludes</td>
      <td class="value">{{rent_excludes}}</td>
    </tr>
    {{/if}}
  </table>

  <h3>Rent Increases</h3>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.5</span> The Landlord may increase the rent by serving at least <strong>3 months' written notice</strong> using the prescribed Rent Increase Notice (Form 4).</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.6</span> Rent may not be increased more than once in any 12-month period.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.7</span> Any increase must not exceed the open market rent for a comparable property.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.8</span> The Tenant may refer a rent increase to a Rent Officer if they believe it is excessive.</p>

  {{#if in_rent_pressure_zone}}
  <div class="legal-notice">
    <div class="legal-notice-title">Rent Pressure Zone</div>
    <p>This property is located in a designated Rent Pressure Zone (RPZ). Rent increases are subject to additional restrictions and caps as set by the local authority.</p>
  </div>
  {{/if}}

  <!-- ===== 6. DEPOSIT ===== -->
  <h2>6. Deposit</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">6.1</span> The Tenant has paid a Deposit of <strong>£{{deposit_amount}}</strong>.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">6.2</span> Within <strong>30 working days</strong> of receiving the deposit, the Landlord will protect it in an approved tenancy deposit scheme and provide the Tenant with the prescribed information.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">6.3</span> The Deposit is held as security for unpaid rent, damage beyond fair wear and tear, unpaid bills, missing inventory items, and other breaches of this agreement.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">6.4</span> Disputes over deductions may be referred to the scheme's free alternative dispute resolution service.</p>

  <table class="data-table">
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Deposit Amount</td>
      <td class="value">£{{deposit_amount}}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Protection Scheme</td>
      <td class="value">{{deposit_scheme_name}}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="label">Protection Deadline</td>
      <td class="value">30 working days from receipt</td>
    </tr>
  </table>

  <div class="legal-notice">
    <div class="legal-notice-title">Approved Scottish Deposit Schemes</div>
    <ul>
      <li>SafeDeposits Scotland</li>
      <li>MyDeposits Scotland</li>
      <li>Letting Protection Service Scotland</li>
    </ul>
    <p>If the Landlord fails to protect the deposit or provide prescribed information, the Tenant may apply to the First-tier Tribunal for an order requiring the Landlord to pay up to three times the deposit amount.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- ===== 7. TENANT OBLIGATIONS ===== -->
  <h2>7. Tenant Obligations</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.1</span> <strong>Rent:</strong> Pay the Rent on time and in full without deduction.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.2</span> <strong>Utilities:</strong> Pay all charges for gas, electricity, water, sewerage, telephone, internet, Council Tax (unless included), and TV licence as set out in Schedule 3.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.3</span> <strong>Principal Home:</strong> Use the property as the Tenant's only or principal home.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.4</span> <strong>Care of Property:</strong> Take reasonable care of the property, keep it clean and tidy, adequately heated and ventilated to prevent condensation and mould.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.5</span> <strong>Reporting Defects:</strong> Report any damage or defects to the Landlord without unreasonable delay.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.6</span> <strong>Damage:</strong> Make good any damage caused by the Tenant, members of the household, or visitors (fair wear and tear excepted).</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.7</span> <strong>Alterations:</strong> Not make alterations, additions, or improvements without the Landlord's prior written consent.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.8</span> <strong>Access:</strong> Allow the Landlord reasonable access (with at least 24 hours' notice except in emergency) for inspections, repairs, or safety checks.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.9</span> <strong>Nuisance:</strong> Not behave antisocially or cause nuisance, annoyance, or disturbance to neighbours.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.10</span> <strong>Business Use:</strong> Not run any business from the property without the Landlord's written consent.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.11</span> <strong>Illegal Use:</strong> Not use the property for any illegal or immoral purpose.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.12</span> <strong>Insurance:</strong> Not do anything that would invalidate the Landlord's insurance. Obtain contents insurance for personal belongings.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.13</span> <strong>Notification:</strong> Notify the Landlord promptly of any damage, defects, change in occupants, or planned absence exceeding {{#if absence_notification_days}}{{absence_notification_days}}{{else}}14{{/if}} days.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.14</span> <strong>End of Tenancy:</strong> Give proper notice (at least 28 days), return the property clean and in comparable condition (fair wear and tear excepted), return all keys, and provide a forwarding address.</p>

  <!-- ===== 8. PROPERTY RULES & RESTRICTIONS ===== -->
  <h2>8. Property Rules and Restrictions</h2>

  <h3>Subletting and Assignment</h3>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.1</span> The Tenant must not sublet the whole property.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.2</span> The Tenant must not sublet part of the property or take in lodgers without the Landlord's prior written consent. Consent must not be unreasonably withheld.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.3</span> The Tenant may request to assign (transfer) the tenancy to another person. The Landlord's consent is required and must not be unreasonably withheld.</p>

  <h3>Pets</h3>
